00:02:32,479 --> 00:02:35,639
 Small talk is an incredibly important function

58
00:02:35,639 --> 00:02:37,479
 of English conversation.

59
00:02:37,479 --> 00:02:38,759
 It's about comfort.

60
00:02:38,759 --> 00:02:40,520
 It's about helping two people,

61
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:43,719
 you and the other person that you're talking to,

62
00:02:43,719 --> 00:02:46,039
 to feel comfortable with each other.

63
00:02:46,039 --> 00:02:49,840
 And the intention is to try and find some common interests,

64
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:52,080
 something that you can share together.

65
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:55,280
 So I wanted to think of yourself as a detective.

66
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:58,759
 You're searching for some information and some clues

67
00:02:58,759 --> 00:03:00,520
 to help you connect with someone,

68
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:03,639
 to find some common ground and share interests.

69
00:03:03,639 --> 00:03:05,280
 A good way to approach small talk

70
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:09,120
 is to focus on a few broad categories.

71
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:14,120
 Work, life, travel, food and the weather.

72
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:17,159
 Now I'm gonna go out on a limb here

73
00:03:17,159 --> 00:03:22,159
 and say that about 90% of all small talk conversations

74
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:25,759
 focus on these topics, maybe even 95.

75
00:03:25,759 --> 00:03:28,560
 But this is great because it allows us to focus

76
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:31,400
 on some really specific topics, right?

77
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:34,159
 And help you to prepare for conversations

78
00:03:34,159 --> 00:03:37,759
 that you're very likely to actually experience.

79
00:03:38,759 --> 00:03:40,240
 There's another thing that's useful

80
00:03:40,240 --> 00:03:43,840
 to keep in mind with small talk and that's time.

81
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:45,360
 With all of these topics,

82
