 we can ask questions that relate to the current situation.

83
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:53,759
 Now, any experience in the past

84
00:03:53,759 --> 00:03:57,199
 or any future dreams or future plans, right?

85
00:03:57,199 --> 00:03:59,439
 So pay close attention to the examples

86
00:03:59,439 --> 00:04:00,759
 that I'm gonna share

87
00:04:00,759 --> 00:04:03,919
 because I'll be using some different time references

88
00:04:03,919 --> 00:04:05,400
 and any questions.

89
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,800
 So let's get started with 30 questions

90
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:11,159
 to help you master small talk conversations.

91
00:04:11,159 --> 00:04:13,120
 Starting with work.

92
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:17,560
 Now, the most common question here is, what do you do?

93
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:21,399
 So we're talking about now, what's their current job?

94
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:23,360
 Imagine that the person that you're talking to

95
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:24,959
 said they're a nurse.

96
00:04:24,959 --> 00:04:27,279
 But we wanna ask some more detail, right?

97
00:04:27,279 --> 00:04:30,560
 We wanna find out how they can continue the conversation.

98
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:31,920
 So let's go back in time.

99
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:36,199
 What motivated you to become a nurse?

100
00:04:36,199 --> 00:04:38,160
 Did you always wanna be a nurse?

101
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:41,759
 What was your first ever job?

102
00:04:41,759 --> 00:04:42,680
 Did you like it?

103
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:46,600
 We can talk about the present as well.

104
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:49,439
 What does your typical workday look like?

105
00:04:49,439 --> 00:04:51,040
 What do you love about your job?

106
00:04:52,399 --> 00:04:53,879
 And you can get a little creative

107
00:04:53,879 --> 00:04:56,040
 with some future questions as well.

108
00:04:57,199 --> 00:04:58,839
 So is this your dream job?

109
00:04:58,839 --> 00:05:01,040
 Are you working towards something else?

110
00:05:02,519 --> 00:05:05,319
 I'm gonna be careful here that you don't say

111
00:05:05,319 --> 00:05:08,240
 working towards something bigger or something better

112
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:10,879
 because it might be a little offensive, right?

113
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,480
 You're sort of saying that their job

114
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:15,439
 that they currently have isn't good enough.

115
00:05:15,439 --> 00:05:18,720
 If money wasn't an issue, what job would you want?

116
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:21,279
 Some people might say that they don't wanna work

117
00:05:21,279 --> 00:05:23,920
 if they didn't have any issues with money, right?

118
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:27,199
 But you might have to rephrase that question and say,

119
00:05:27,199 --> 00:05:28,600
 well, what would you do?

120
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,759
 Or how would you spend your time?

121
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:33,959
 Another really great small talk topic

122
00:05:33,959 --> 00:05:36,319
 is just talking about life.

123
00:05:36,319 --> 00:05:39,160
 And there's a couple of ways that you can do this.

124
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:42,560
 You can pay attention to local news headlines.

125
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:46,279
 This is a really good way of finding things to talk about.

126
00:05:47,399 --> 00:05:51,399
 Did you hear about the accident on the freeway last night?

127
00:05:51,399 --> 00:05:52,519
 Sounded awful.

128
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:55,759
 I got stuck in traffic for over two hours.

129
00:05:55,759 --> 00:05:58,639
 Albeit you might end up talking a lot

130
00:05:58,639 --> 00:06:01,800
 about all of the negative stuff that was in your news, right?

131
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:04,600
 But you can also ask questions

132
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:07,360
 about what's happening in a person's life.

133
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:09,759
 So remember that your intention is to try and find

134
00:06:09,759 --> 00:06:11,399
 some common interests, right?

135
00:06:11,399 --> 00:06:13,639
 Some things that you share

136
00:06:13,639 --> 00:06:16,439
 so that you can keep talking about those things together.

137
00:06:18,439 --> 00:06:20,560
 Have you got much planned for the weekend?

138
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:22,560
 This is a great question.

139
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:23,759
 It's my go-to.

140
00:06:23,759 --> 00:06:26,560
 Everyone loves talking about their plans on the weekend.

141
00:06:28,519 --> 00:06:30,639
 What do you like to do in your spare time?

142
00:06:31,920 --> 00:06:34,920
 Now, if they share something that you also like,

143
00:06:34,959 --> 00:06:36,879
 that's great because you can keep talking

144
00:06:36,879 --> 00:06:39,079
 about your shared interests.

145
00:06:39,079 --> 00:06:42,399
 Or if they share something that you don't know anything about,

146
00:06:42,399 --> 00:06:44,959
 ask them for more information.

147
00:06:44,959 --> 00:06:46,720
 Oh, that's so interesting.

148
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:49,000
 I've never met anyone who keeps bees

149
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,519
 and makes their own honey.

150
00:06:50,519 --> 00:06:52,680
 How much honey do you get each week?

151
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:54,639
 Have you ever been bitten by a bee?

152
00:06:54,639 --> 00:06:57,959
 Is it easy to keep bees or do you have to be an expert?

153
00:07:01,160 --> 00:07:03,040
 Have you read any good books lately?

154
00:07:04,040 --> 00:07:06,120
 Have you seen any good movies?

155
00:07:06,120 --> 00:07:07,600
 If you're a mom or you're a dad,

156
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:11,240
 you might even ask, so do you have any kids?

157
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:15,439
 Because this is a great way to connect with someone.

158
00:07:15,439 --> 00:07:18,959
 Talk about your kids' ages, interests,

159
00:07:18,959 --> 00:07:20,839
 maybe even their minority habits.

160
00:07:20,839 --> 00:07:22,560
 Same thing with pets, actually.

161
00:07:23,439 --> 00:07:26,720
 Have you noticed that I've been using so quite a bit

162
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:29,839
 to introduce a new idea to a conversation?

163
00:07:29,839 --> 00:07:31,920
 This is really quite a natural way

164
00:07:31,959 --> 00:07:34,240
 to introduce a new question.

165
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:37,040
 One that's unrelated to what you've been talking about

166
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:40,879
 previous, it's a really helpful conversation tool.

167
00:07:40,879 --> 00:07:42,720
 So are you from here?

168
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:47,720
 This is a great question to help explore someone's past,

169
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:49,519
 go back in time.

170
00:07:49,519 --> 00:07:51,199
 Where did you live before this?

171
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:56,839
 Is this city quite different to that city?

172
00:07:58,519 --> 00:07:59,600
 Where did you grow up?

173
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:02,879
 Travel is a great small talk topic.

174
00:08:02,879 --> 00:08:04,959
 It's something that we love talking about

175
00:08:04,959 --> 00:08:06,519
 and we love sharing.

176
00:08:06,519 --> 00:08:09,480
 So we can talk about our past experience

177
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:11,839
 or we can talk about travel plans

178
00:08:11,839 --> 00:08:14,480
 and dreams for the future, right?

179
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:16,800
 If you're coming up to a holiday season,

180
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:18,360
 you're heading into summer,

181
00:08:18,360 --> 00:08:21,800
 then a great conversation starter is,

182
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:24,920
 so are you planning on getting away for the holidays?

183
00:08:27,079 --> 00:08:29,079
 Are you taking time off over Christmas?

184
00:08:29,879 --> 00:08:32,039
 Or whatever holidays coming up?

185
00:08:33,279 --> 00:08:35,240
 But if it's not that time of year,

186
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:37,440
 you can easily start a conversation

187
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:39,960
 by introducing some context, right?

188
00:08:39,960 --> 00:08:43,000
 By sharing your experience first

189
